Pairplot

#-----Helper functions-----
panel.cor <- function(x,y, digits=2, prefix="", cex.cor){
  usr <- par("usr")
  on.exit(par(usr))
  par(usr = c(0,1,0,1))
  r <- abs(cor(x,y,use="complete.obs"))
  txt <- format(c(r,0.123456789), digits = digits)[1]
  txt <- paste0(prefix, txt,sep="")
  if(missing(cex.cor)) cex.cor <- 0.8/strwidth(txt)
  text(0.5, 0.5, txt, cex = cex.cor * (1 + r) / 2)
}

panel.hist <- function(x, ...){
  usr <- par("usr")
  on.exit(par(usr))
  par(usr = c(usr[1:2],0,1.5))
  h <- hist(x, plot = FALSE)
  breaks <- h$breaks
  nB <- length(breaks)
  y <- h$counts
  y <- y/max(y)
  rect(breaks[-nB], 0, breaks[-1], y, col="white",...)
}

panel.lm <- function(x, y, col = par("col"), bg = NA, pch = par("pch"),
                     cex = 1, col.smooth = "blue", ...) {
  points(x, y, pch = pch, col = col, bg = bg, cex = cex)
  abline(stats::lm(x ~ y), col = "steelblue", ...)
}

Hypotzy, ktor sa nm zdaj zaujmav:

Koeficient GDP (0.135) je tatisticky vznamn (p-hodnota < 0.001), o naznauje pozitvnu a siln zvislos medzi percentulnymi vdavkami na jedlo a GDP krajiny.

Shapiro-Wilkov test normality rezidu odmieta nulov hypotzu o normlnej distribcii rezidu (p-hodnota < 0.001). To naznauje, e rezidu nie s z normlneho rozdelenia. Suma tvorcov rezidu (RSS) je 1785839046. RMSE, o je tandardn miera presnosti modelu, je pribline 1999.93. Meme potvrdi hypotzu, e vdavky na jedlo svisia s HDP krajiny.
